ccurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Old German: Mighty battle maid"]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":3,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":34,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda Cheshire was born about 1256, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with John de Timperley. She died in 1301, in Cheshire, England, at the age of 46."},"et":{"abt 1256–1301":"umbes 1256–1301","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1290–1351":"1290–1351","1256–1301":"1256–1301","1259":"1259","1301":"1301","1256":"1256","1255":"1255","1351":"1351","abt 1256":"umbes 1256","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Timperley, Cheshire, England":"Timperley, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"abt 1256–1301":"noin 1256–1301","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1290–1351":"1290–1351","1256–1301":"1256–1301","1259":"1259","1301":"1301","1256":"1256","1255":"1255","1351":"1351","abt 1256":"noin 1256","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Timperley, Cheshire, England":"Timperley, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"abt 1256–1301":"environ 1256–1301","1255–1301":"1255–1301","1290–1351":"1290–1351","1256–1301":"1256–1301","1259":"1259","1301":"1301","1256":"1256","1255":"1255","1351":"1351","abt 1256":"environ 1256","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre","Timperley, Cheshire,